<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Table-Not-Found on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/table-not-found/</link><description>Recent content in Table-Not-Found on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/table-not-found/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Java SQLException: Table Not Found / Connection Refused Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/sql-exception/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/sql-exception/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sqlexception-table-not-found--connection-refused"&gt;SQLException: Table Not Found / Connection Refused&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;java.sql.SQLException&lt;/code&gt; is a checked exception that provides information about database access errors. Common variants include &amp;ldquo;table not found,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;connection refused,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;connection reset,&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;communication link failure.&amp;rdquo; These errors indicate problems at the database layer rather than application logic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;SQLException&lt;/code&gt; is the parent exception for all JDBC database errors. It contains a SQL state code, vendor-specific error code, and a descriptive message. The SQL state follows the XOPEN/SQL:1999 standard and helps identify the category of error.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Table Doesn't Exist Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-table-not-found-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-table-not-found-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sql-table-doesnt-exist-error-fix"&gt;SQL Table Doesn&amp;rsquo;t Exist Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A SQL table not found error occurs when a query references a table that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist in the current database or schema.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The database cannot find the specified table. This happens when the table hasn&amp;rsquo;t been created, you&amp;rsquo;re using the wrong database/schema, or the table name is misspelled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Table not created yet (missing migration/DDL)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong database or schema selected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typo in table name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Table was dropped&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing schema prefix&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-which-database-is-selected"&gt;1. Check which database is selected&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Verify current database
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DATABASE&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- MySQL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; current_database(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- PostgreSQL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Use fully qualified name
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; mydb.mytable &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; id &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-list-available-tables"&gt;2. List available tables&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Show tables in current database
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; TABLES; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- MySQL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;dt &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- PostgreSQL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;table_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; information_schema.tables
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; table_schema &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;public&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- PostgreSQL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-create-table-if-missing"&gt;3. Create table if missing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Create table
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CREATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TABLE&lt;/span&gt; users (
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; id INT &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;PRIMARY&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;KEY&lt;/span&gt; AUTO_INCREMENT,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; name VARCHAR(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;255&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;NOT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;NULL&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; email VARCHAR(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;255&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;UNIQUE&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; created_at &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TIMESTAMP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DEFAULT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CURRENT_TIMESTAMP&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-use-correct-schema-prefix"&gt;4. Use correct schema prefix&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- WRONG: Missing schema
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Include schema when needed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;.users; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- PostgreSQL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; dbo.users; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- SQL Server
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="sql-column-not-found-v2"&gt;SQL Column Not Found&lt;/a&gt; — column missing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="sql-syntax-error-v2"&gt;SQL Syntax Error&lt;/a&gt; — syntax issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="sql-access-denied-v2"&gt;SQL Access Denied&lt;/a&gt; — permission errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Table Not Found Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-table-not-found/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-table-not-found/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a SQL query references a table that does not exist in the current database. The message reads: &lt;code&gt;Table 'X' doesn't exist&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The database cannot find the specified table in the current schema. This can happen because the table was never created, was dropped, or you&amp;rsquo;re using the wrong database name.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Table was never created or was dropped&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong database selected (&lt;code&gt;USE database_name&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Table name misspelled in the query&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Table exists in a different schema&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-available-tables"&gt;Fix 1: Check available tables&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; TABLES;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- or
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;table_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; information_schema.tables
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; table_schema &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DATABASE&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-verify-database-selection"&gt;Fix 2: Verify database selection&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;USE my_database;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; TABLES;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Now query the correct table
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-check-for-table-name-case-sensitivity"&gt;Fix 3: Check for table name case sensitivity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Some databases are case-sensitive
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Wrong on Linux MySQL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; Users;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ERROR 1146: Table &amp;#39;shop.orders&amp;#39; doesn&amp;#39;t exist
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Fix: check the correct database
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;USE ecommerce;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; TABLES;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="column-not-found.md"&gt;Column Not Found&lt;/a&gt; — the table exists but column doesn&amp;rsquo;t&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="syntax-error.md"&gt;Syntax Error&lt;/a&gt; — malformed SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Table Not Found Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/table-not-found/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/table-not-found/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sql-table-not-found-error-fix"&gt;SQL Table Not Found Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a SQL statement references a table that does not exist in the current database. The message reads: &lt;code&gt;Table 'X' doesn't exist&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the database engine tries to resolve the table name in a query, it checks the current database&amp;rsquo;s table catalog. If the table is missing, misspelled, or belongs to a different database, this error is raised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Typo in table name&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;usres&lt;/code&gt; instead of &lt;code&gt;users&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wrong database context&lt;/strong&gt; — the table exists in a different database.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Table was dropped or not yet created&lt;/strong&gt; — schema migration hasn&amp;rsquo;t run.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing schema prefix&lt;/strong&gt; — cross-database query needs &lt;code&gt;database.table&lt;/code&gt; syntax.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-verify-the-table-exists"&gt;Fix 1: Verify the table exists&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- List all tables in the current database
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; TABLES;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Check a specific table
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; TABLES &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;LIKE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;users%&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-the-database-context"&gt;Fix 2: Check the database context&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- See which database you&amp;#39;re using
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DATABASE&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Switch to the correct database
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;USE my_database;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Or qualify with the database name
